<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="64" type="diagnostic characters">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="64">
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="64" start="start">Diagnostic</pageBreakToken>
characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="64">Body length 4.4-4.8 mm. Pronotum subquadrate, with rounded anterior and posterior angles, surface flat and with sparse and fine punctation. Elytra with distinct punctural rows without striae, size of the punctures diminishing laterally and apically. Aedeagus not examined herein (because of the fragility of the type). It is said (but not figured) in the description, that the apicale is short and acute at the tip, and the basale is long and bent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
